9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to insurance; prohibiting insurers
from increasing motor vehicle liability premiums
11 based solely on removal of deceased spouse from
policy; clarifying removal of a deceased spouse shall
12 not be treated as a material change; clarifying
section does not prevent increasing premiums at
13 renewal for other reasons; establishing that any
increase in violation shall be void; providing for
14 codification; and providing an effective date.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6093 of Title 36, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 It shall be unlawful for any insurer to increase a motor vehicle
22 liability insurance policy premium based solely on the removal by a
23 named insured of a deceased spouse from the policy. The removal of
24 a deceased spouse shall not be treated as a material change in risk
HB3802 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 for purposes of underwriting, rating classification, or premium
2 calculation. Nothing in this section shall be construed as to
3 prevent insurers from increasing premiums at renewal based on either
4 documented changes in driving record, claims history, coverage
5 elections, mileage, garaging location, or other actuarially
6 supported risk factors; or rate changes approved by the Oklahoma
7 Insurance Department that are applied uniformly to a class of
8 insureds. Any premium increase imposed in violation of this section
9 shall be void and unenforceable, and the insurer shall refund any
10 excess premium collected.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
12
